389. membranis ‘the parchments'. Usually membrana denotes the parchment case or wrapping of the papyrus roll, which formed the liber: cp. Ellis on Catuli. XXII. 7, with Munro on Catullus p. 53 (quoted on Ep. 1. 13, 6); but that meaning is out of the question here.
